<BaseLayout title="About" description="GameTestersHub is your honest guide to earning money through gaming. No hype, no BS — just real reviews and practical advice.">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px; padding: 60px 24px;">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h1>About GameTestersHub</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="article-content">
      <p>GameTestersHub started with a simple question: <strong>can you actually earn money playing games?</strong></p>
      <p>The answer is yes — but not the way most sites tell you. We got tired of seeing "make $50/hour playing games!" clickbait that leads to garbage survey sites and broken promises. So we built the resource we wished existed.</p>

      <h2>What We Do</h2>
      <p>We review every earning platform, rewards site, and game testing opportunity we can find. We sign up, use them, track our earnings, and report what actually works. No affiliate deal changes our rating — if a platform is bad, we say so.</p>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Honest reviews</strong> — we include cons, not just pros</li>
        <li><strong>Real earnings data</strong> — we track $/hour, not just total payouts</li>
        <li><strong>Practical guides</strong> — actionable advice, not motivational fluff</li>
        <li><strong>Regular updates</strong> — platforms change; our reviews keep up</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Make Money</h2>
      <p>Transparency matters. We earn commissions when you sign up for platforms through our links. This doesn't cost you anything extra — the platforms pay us for referring users. We review platforms regardless of whether they have affiliate programs, and our ratings aren't for sale.</p>

      <h2>Get Started</h2>
      <p>New here? Start with our <a href="/guides/truth-about-game-testing">guide on the truth about game testing</a>, or jump straight to our <a href="/reviews">platform reviews</a> to find where to earn.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
